        "notes": "Supports assignment to non-computed member targets and returns the assigned value (JavaScript assignment-expression semantics), including chained assignment patterns where the result is consumed (e.g., exports = module.exports = {...}; fixes #558). Emitted via JavaScriptRuntime.Object.SetItem(obj, key, value) with a string key. Supports ExpandoObject (object literals) and reflection-backed host objects; strings are treated as immutable and ignore writes. Strict assignment to read-only intrinsic, built-in, and inherited data properties such as Math.PI, Function.length, and non-writable prototype properties throws TypeError."
